# Basic globs (bash/zsh)
*                       any string
?                       single character
[abc]                   character class
[a-z]                   range
[^...] or [!...]        negated class

# Extended globs (zsh: setopt extended_glob)
*.(mpg|mov)             multiple extensions
^*.log                  negation (not ending in .log)
**/*                    recursive glob
foo*~*.txt              glob exclusion (matches foo* but not *.txt)
<x-y>                   numeric ranges

# Examples
# Basic
*.txt                    # all .txt files
image?.png               # image + 1 char + .png (e.g., image1.png)
image[0-9].png           # image0.png through image9.png
image[0-9][0-9].png      # image00.png through image99.png

# Extended glob (zsh: setopt extended_glob)
*.(mpg|mov|avi)          # video files
^*.log                   # everything except .log files
**/*.zsh                 # recursive - all .zsh files in subdirs
*.png~thumbnail_*.png    # .png files but not thumbnails
<1-100>                  # match numbers 1-100
image<1-100>.png         # image001.png through image100.png

# Qualifiers (zsh)
*(.)                     # regular files only
*(@)                     # symbolic links only
*/                       # directories only
*(om)                    # sorted by modification time (newest first)
*(.Lm+10)                # files larger than 10MB
